  "text": "(1.1) (Such a pair is called unstable.) In the absence of infinite descending chains the mutual nearest neighbour matching shows that a stable matching exists and is almost surely uniquely determined; see [CITATION_1] and Section 3. In this paper we study the point process Ψ τ := {τ (p) : p ∈ Φ} = {x ∈ Ψ : τ (x) = ∞}; a stable thinning of Ψ. Figures 1 and  2 show realizations of Ψ τ when Ψ is a stationary Poisson point process in 1D and 2D, respectively.",
